---
description: Command class conventions — do not use sealed on ICommand types
globs: src/Modules/**/Commands/**/*Command.cs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Commands

- Do **not** add the `sealed` keyword to command classes (`ICommand<T>`) in any module.
- Use `public class {Name}Command : ICommand<...>` (handlers may still use `sealed` where appropriate).
